<h1>Problem 475 - 2012 USAMO, P3 of 3, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Determine which integers \(n > 1\) have the property that there exists an infinite sequence \(a_1, a_2, a_3, \ldots\) of nonzero integers such that the equality\[a_k+2a_{2k}+\ldots+na_{nk}=0\]holds for every positive integer \(k\).</p>
